{{confuse|Mythologies (book)}} {{Refimprove|date=July 2009}}
{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Mythology: Timeless Tales of Gods and Heroes | image = File:MythologyBook.jpg | image_size = 175 | alt = | caption = First edition | author = [[Edith Hamilton]] | illustrator = [[Steele Savage]] | cover_artist = | country = | language = | subject = [[Greek mythology]], [[Roman mythology]], and [[Norse mythology]] | genre = | publisher = [[Little, Brown and Company]] | pub_date = 1942 | media_type = | pages = xiv, 497 pages | awards = | dewey = | congress = }}
'''''Mythology: Timeless Tales of Gods and Heroes''''' is a book written by [[Edith Hamilton]], published in 1942 by [[Little, Brown and Company]]. It has been reissued since then by several publishers. It retells stories of [[Greek mythology|Greek]], [[Roman mythology|Roman]], and [[Norse mythology|Norse]] [[mythology]] drawn from a variety of sources. The introduction includes commentary on the major classical poets used as sources, and on how changing cultures have led to changing characterizations of the deities and their myths. It is frequently used in high schools and colleges as an introductory text to ancient mythology and belief.
== Contents == The book contains an introduction and seven sections:<ref>Edith Hamilton, ''Mythology'', Little, Brown and Company, 1942.</ref> #Greek gods of [[Mount Olympus|Olympus]] and the Greek [[Greek mythology#Cosmogony and cosmology|creation myths]] #Greek and Roman myths involving love and adventure, including the tales of [[Eros and Psyche]] and [[Jason]]'s quest for the [[Golden Fleece]] #Heroes before the [[Trojan War]], such as [[Perseus]], [[Theseus]], [[Heracles]] and [[Atalanta]] #Trojan War and its heroes, including [[Odysseus]], [[Aeneas]] and [[Achilles]] #Significant families in Greek mythology: the house of [[Atreus]], the royal house of [[Ancient Thebes (Boeotia)|Thebes]], and the royal house of [[Athens]] #Lesser-known stories from Greek and Roman mythology #Tales from Norse myths involving deities such as [[Odin]], [[Thor]] and [[Loki]]
Most editions include drawings by American illustrator [[Steele Savage]].
