'''Pricena'''(Arabic: برايسنا) is a [[shopping comparison engine]] serving the Middle East. The site was initially launched in 2013 in the [[United Arab Emirates]], then expanded to [[Egypt]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Kuwait]], and [[Qatar]], as well as [[Nigeria]], [[South Africa]], and [[India]]. The origin of the name Pricena (pronounced ''Price-na'') comes from a contraction of the words "Price" and "na", the latter meaning "our" in Arabic, thus forming "Our Price". The site allows online shoppers to compare prices of more than one million products from over 200 stores across the Middle East.
== History == Below are the major milestones for Pricena:
* July 2013: Pricena was launched as a website in July 2013 in Dubai. * January 2014: Pricena launches its website in Saudi Arabia with Arabic support.<ref name="saudi" /> * July 2014: Pricena launches in Egypt * May 2015: Pricena launches its iOS app * August 2015: Pricena launches its Android app * December 2015: Pricena launches in Kuwait.<ref name="kuwait" />
== Online Startup of the Year 2015 Award == In November 2015, Pricena was recognized as the Online Startup of the Year for 2015 by Du Enterprise Agility Awards.<ref name="award" /> The award’s criteria were based on a ''startup’s purpose to solve a specific and clear regional problem, its ability to attract a sizable audience and its potential to further grow in the region and beyond''.
== References == {{reflist|refs= <ref name="saudi">{{cite web|title=UAE's price comparison website steps into Saudi Arabia|url=http://www.wamda.com/2015/01/price-comparison-website-pricena-sets-foot-in-saudi-arabia|website=Wamda}}</ref> <ref name="kuwait">{{cite web|title=Leading Middle East shopping comparison site Pricena.com launched in Kuwait|url=http://mid-east.info/leading-middle-east-shopping-comparison-site-pricena-com-launches-in-kuwait-40786/|website=Mid East Information}}</ref> <ref name="award">{{cite web|title=The Recap: Enterprise Agility Awards 2015|url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/254208|website=Entrepreneur.com}}</ref> }}
